dcterms:description: The COVID-19 Radiography Database is the most comprehensive collection of COVID-19 chest X-ray images, stemming from different databases around the web. It offers chest X-rays of 3,616 COVID-19 positive, 10,192 Normal, and 1,345 Pneumonia cases.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 Radiography Database

dcterms:description: The Chest X-Ray Images (Pneumonia) dataset offers X-ray images divided into two classes with 1,583 Normal and 4,273 Pneumonia samples. It is used to evaluate models for pneumonia detection.
dcterms:title: Chest X-Ray Images (Pneumonia)

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a vast collection counting 14 million images and covering 20,000 categories from general to specific. It is commonly used for pre-training models in various image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: The MNIST Database offers a large image collection of handwritten digits, providing 60,000 images for training and 10,000 for testing. It is commonly used as a benchmark in image classification.
dcterms:title: MNIST Database
